{"word":"G4352 - προσκυνέω - proskynéō - pros-koo-neh'-o - Worship","slug":"G4352","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">προσκυνέω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>proskynéō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>pros-koo-neh'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Worship"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C0;&#x03C1;&#x03BF;&#x03C3;&#x03BA;&#x03C5;&#x03BD;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03C9; - proskuneo&#x0304;</b> - <i>pros-koo-neh'-o</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G4314\">G4314</a> and probably a derivative of <a href=\"#/G2965\">G2965</a> (meaning to <i>kiss</i>, like a dog <i>licking</i> his master&rsquo;s hand); to <i>fawn</i> or <i>crouch to</i>, that is, (literally or figuratively) <i>prostrate</i> oneself in homage (<i>do reverence</i> to, <i>adore</i>): - worship."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G4353\">G4353</a>"}]}